
Author: Khalid Romain
 
TITLE: Fin-tech Case Study in the Domain of Reg-tech: Trulioo

Overview and Origin 

1.1 Name of company: Trulioo

1.2 When was the company incorporated?:
      Founded in 2011 by Stephen Ufford

1.3 How did the idea for the company (or project) come about?

According to Stephen Ufford, founder of Trulioo, in an article entitled “The 2 Surprising Keys To Building A Good Unicorn? Authenticity And Perseverance”, 
published in Forbes Magazine, he said that trust seemed to be the missing ingredient that would make the most positive impact on the internet. 
For this reason he created a company that produced a product that can ensure trust at scale, thus solving many issues in large and small corporations.

1.4 Is the company funded? How much funding have they received?

  Latest funding $394m 
  Total funding $477.7m

1.5 Trulioo investors : Goldman Sachs, bdc venture capital, American Express, Blumberg   capital, Citi ventures

2. Business Activities:

2.1 What specific financial problem is the company or project trying to solve? 

Trulioo Is an online verification company. It helps banks, financial service providers, online marketplaces,
and others verify the identity of their customers. Using hundreds of data sources.

2.2 Who is the company's intended customer?  Is there any information about the market size of this set of customers?

Banks , financial service providers, online marketplaces are its customers . To date, Trulioo customers were reported to be 5 Billion.

2.3 What solution does this company offer that their competitors do not or cannot offer? (What is the unfair advantage they utilize?)

Many people around the world today don’t have an identity record. Without an identity record, they are deemed untrustworthy for the most basic 
and critical transactions required for success in our digital world. This is the problem Trulioo is trying to solve, Equal access to identity 
verification for all. 

2.4 Which technologies are they currently using, and how are they implementing them? (This may take a little bit of sleuthing–– you may want to search the company’s engineering blog or use sites like Stackshare to find this information.)

They have API integration, custom rules engine, normalized fields/attributes and other technologies that are all about flexibility for their customers. 
They also use Artificial Intelligence (AI) which allows them to perform link analysis, pattern recognition and workflow automation among other things, 
which aids in the successful implementation of Know your customer processes and Anti money laundering regulations.

3 Landscape:

3.1 What domain of the financial industry is the company in?

Trulioo belongs to the Regtech domain of the financial industry.

3.2 What have been the major trends and innovations of this domain over the last 5-10 years?

Some of the Major trends in this domain include:
Outsourcing Reporting : According to an article by Trudy Namer (Top Ten Regtech Trends for 2020 and Beyond) on the Cappitech by IHS Market website, 
companies are moving towards using vendor solutions , as internal reporting solutions don’t provide any competitive edge nor does the increased cost of 
doing it inadequately provide any benefit. The move is as a result of regulatory requirements increasing across jurisdictions and thus increasing the cost 
and scale of solutions.

Balancing Privacy with Surveillance : Firms have to now be careful not to infringe upon the privacy of consumers when it comes to data storage, 
processing and investigation.

Crypto & the AML Regulation : As the industry develops, greater regulations have been imposed to prevent fraud and the incidence of
money laundering therefore requiring more disclosure in terms of crypto transfers.

3.3 What are the other major companies in this domain?

Some of Trulioo in the regtech industry include: Zighra Technology, Urjanet Technology, Sterling Technology and Verify Technology to name a few.

4 Results

4.1 What has been the business impact of this company so far?

The greatest business impact of Trulioo so far is that it has managed to obtain over 5 billion (customers) verified identities to the internet. 
Thereby creating a more trustworthy virtual market.

4.2 What are some of the core metrics that companies in this domain use to measure success? How is your company performing, based on these metrics?

According to the craft.co website three core metrics that companies in this domain use to measure success are; Countries covered, 
Customers, and Enterprise Customers. Thus far, Trulioo is performing well with having customers amounting to 5 billion in 195 countries
and 295 of those 5 billion customers being Enterprise Customers.

4.3 How is your company performing relative to competitors in the same domain?

Trulioo compared to other competitors in the same domain appears to be an industry leader and is now valued at $1.75 Billion dollars.


5 Recommendations

5.1 If you were to advise the company, what products or services would you suggest they offer? (This could be something that a competitor offers, 
or use your imagination!)
Given the trying times the world has experienced due to the Covid 19 pandemic, it may be worthwhile for Trulioo to propose or explore the development 
of a digital vaccination passport or vaccination identification, compatible with portable phones. It is a product that will have world-wide demand and
can be treated similarly to the “identity at scale” service they already provide.

5.2 Why do you think that offering this product or service would benefit the company?
 One of the company’s milestones as stated by its founder is to eventually be able to provide 7 billion customers virtual identities. Currently, 
 the company is at 5 billion. Offering a product such as a Covid-19 vaccine passport (Vaccine Identity) to the world would attract more people to their
 service since world governments are issuing vaccine mandates for their citizens to live within society and travel outside of their jurisdiction. 
 Offering such a product may bring them closer to increasing market share, increase wealth and have a positive social and health impact on the world.

5.3 What technologies would this additional product or service utilize?
The purpose for choosing this product is because it can be treated similarly to identity verification and therefore no additional technology is required. 
They can bring this idea to fruition with the technology they already possess.




